((select id from decks where slug = 'self-love'), 'sacred-embrace', 30, 'Sacred Embrace', 'Notice what relaxes your body when no one is watching. Let your inner world feel less crowded and more kind.', 'The heart opens more easily when it does not feel judged for being human. For now, trust that small acts of gentleness can still change your day.', 'self-love', 'self-trust', 'self-love/sacred-embrace', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'self-love'), 'sacred-bloom', 31, 'Sacred Bloom', 'Care becomes clearer when you stop withholding it from yourself. As you move through today, protect your peace before you explain it away.', 'A steadier relationship with yourself is built through repeated moments of honesty and care. If it feels supportive, choose language that leaves you feeling safe inside your own mind.', 'self-love', 'soft reset', 'self-love/sacred-bloom', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-waters', 32, 'Quiet Waters', 'Healing does not always look dramatic when it is truly working. Release the timeline that keeps asking your pain to hurry.', 'The nervous system responds to consistency long before it responds to pressure. Allow enough rest for insight to arrive naturally.', 'healing', 'emotional release', 'healing/quiet-waters', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-release', 33, 'Quiet Release', 'A small exhale can be a meaningful turning point. A tender season still counts as forward movement.', 'Some chapters end when you stop demanding certainty from your own process. For now, honor what feels fragile without making it permanent.', 'healing', 'renewal', 'healing/quiet-release', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-mending', 34, 'Quiet Mending', 'You are allowed to recover without proving how strong you are. As you move through today, let yourself receive support without apologizing for needing it.', 'True healing makes room for complexity, because not every wound closes in a straight line. If it feels supportive, return to what helps you feel regulated and present.', 'healing', 'soft reset', 'healing/quiet-mending', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-lantern', 35, 'Quiet Lantern', 'The parts of you that feel tired deserve gentleness, not urgency. For now, you can honor what happened without staying inside it forever.', 'Recovery is shaped by safety, rest, and the willingness to stop turning pain into identity. In this moment, let your next act be soothing rather than proving.', 'healing', 'protection', 'healing/quiet-lantern', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-breath', 36, 'Quiet Breath', 'Repair often begins in places that finally feel safe enough to soften. Release the timeline that keeps asking your pain to hurry.', 'What has been tender can still become wise, spacious, and beautifully alive again. Offer yourself a softer landing than yesterday.', 'healing', 'restoration', 'healing/quiet-breath', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-tide', 37, 'Quiet Tide', 'A small exhale can be a meaningful turning point. What aches can still become a doorway to deeper honesty.', 'When your inner world feels seen instead of pushed, repair becomes more possible. For now, make space for a slower, steadier kind of repair.', 'healing', 'gentle repair', 'healing/quiet-tide', true),
((select id from decks where slug = 'healing'), 'quiet-threshold', 38, 'Quiet Threshold', 'There is dignity in moving at the speed your heart can trust. As you move through today, let yourself receive support without apologizing for needing it.', 'Your heart can carry memory without being ruled by it. If it feels supportive, choose one grounding ritual that helps your body feel less alone.', 'healing', 'emotional release', 'healing/quiet-threshold', true),
